2.2.3.1 Perceptions related to the Government
When asked to briefly describe the Government position in the Solomon Islands, many of the respondents expressed hope and were optimistic about some government priorities related to the country’s development, but perceived that there was too much corruption and people were living in poverty. Their answers neo colonialism and political instability as being key factors affecting the political climate of the country and contributing towards widespread poverty, unemployment and dissatisfaction.
